Cloud Characteristics - as per NIST

1. On - Demand Self service
2. Broad Network Access
3. Resource pooling
4. Rapid Elasticity
5. Measured Service

hypervisor - special os that helps normal os to run.
In cloud you always get a virtual machine. Some company also gives - bare metal server (physical servers)

Multi tenant  - vm belongs to different accounts but using same hypervisor.
Single tenant - vm belongs to single account on a physical server.

Virtualization at Storage - RAID
Storage are real from where we can carve out virtual disk for storage. (Volume Manager)
Enterprise storage is always virtual - volumes (no physical disk)
